<node TEXT="Implementation" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_757766181" CREATED="1504810976605" MODIFIED="1504811006005">
<node TEXT="Converts calls/min to mins between calls" ID="ID_1004207552" CREATED="1504811006796" MODIFIED="1504811205076"><richcontent TYPE="NOTE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      So <i>60 calls per min </i>effectively gets converted into <i>a minimum of 1 sec between 2 calls</i>. Hence you can only send 1 call per second
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      The policy just looks at the previous call timestamp and decides whether to allow this one.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
